  "prompt": "How do I know if some one has read my direct message on instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can tell if someone has read your direct message (DM) based on a couple of indicators:\n\n1. **Seen Status**: If the recipient has read your message, you will see the word \"Seen\" along with a timestamp below your message. This indicates the exact time they viewed your message.\n\n2. **Read Receipts**: Read receipts are typically enabled by default. However, if the recipient has disabled them in their privacy settings, you won't see the \"Seen\" status even if they have read your message.\n\n3. **Message Interaction**: If the user has interacted with your message (e.g., reacted to it with an emoji), you will also know they have seen it.\n\nIf you don\u2019t see these indicators, it either means they haven\u2019t read your message or they have disabled read receipts.",
